view.name: MTA Subway Entrances and Exits: 2024
view.description: This is a dataset containing the entrances and exits at New York City Subway and Staten Island Railway stations. Information is provided on the entrance or exit, including their coordinates, the borough they are in, whether it allows entries and exits, and the type of entrance (more information below). The dataset also includes the name of the station complex, the complex ID number, the name of the specific station in the complex the entrance is for (constituent station), the station ID number, the GTFS Stop ID, the daytime routes that stop at the station complex, and the line and division the constituent station is on.

columns.name: Division
columns.description: The division of the subway system (IRT, BMT, IND, SIR) that the station is a part of.

columns.name: Line
columns.description: The operational line of the subway system the station is located on, such as Queens Blvd, Lexington Av, or Sea Beach.

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: Represents the five boroughs of New York City (Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens, Staten Island).

columns.name: Stop Name
columns.description: The name of the subway station/station complex.

top.item: Times Sq-42 St/Port Authority Bus Terminal

columns.name: Complex ID
columns.description: The Complex ID, or its Complex Master Reference Number.

columns.name: Constituent Station Name
columns.description: The name of the specific subway station (or specific station in a complex) the entrance is to.

columns.name: Station ID
columns.description: The ID, or Master Reference Number, for the station.

columns.name: GTFS Stop ID
columns.description: The GTFS Stop ID or IDs for the station.

columns.name: Daytime Routes
columns.description: The subway routes that serve the station during weekdays.

columns.name: Entrance Type
columns.description: The type of entrance (Stair, Escalator, Elevator, Station House, Walkway, Ramp, Overpass, Underpass, Easement – Street, Easement – Passage, Stair/Escalator, Stair/Ramp, Stair/Ramp/Walkway).

columns.name: Entry Allowed
columns.description: Whether or not entries are allowed at this entrance/exit.

columns.name: Exit Allowed
columns.description: Whether or not exits are allowed at this entrance/exit.

columns.name: Entrance Latitude
columns.description: The latitude for the station entrance.

columns.name: Entrance Longitude
columns.description: The longitude for the station entrance.

columns.name: entrance_georeference
columns.description: Open Data platform-generated geocoding information from supplied address components for stations. Point-type location is the centroid of the address components provided and does not reflect a specific address if the street address component is not provided. Point-type location is supplied in "POINT ( )" format.
